# Deployment Rules

## Single Deployment Target (DO NOT CHANGE)

This project deploys to **exactly one** Vercel project, on **one** team:

- **Vercel team**: `lovedesignwork-8523s-projects` (lovedesignwork-8523's projects)
- **Vercel project**: `royalwellnessspa`
- **Production URL**: `https://royalwellnessspa.vercel.app`
- **Deployment URL**: `https://royalwellnessspa-qpzawfmey-lovedesignwork-8523s-projects.vercel.app`
- **GitHub repo**: `https://github.com/lovedesignwork/royalwellnessspa.git` (branch: `main`)

## Deployment Method: GitHub Only

- Deploy ONLY by pushing to GitHub `main`. Vercel's GitHub integration will auto-build and deploy.
- The deploy workflow is:
  1. `git add -A`
  2. `git commit -m "..."`
  3. `git push origin main`
  4. Vercel automatically deploys.

## Forbidden Actions

- DO NOT run `vercel deploy`, `vercel deploy --prod`, or any Vercel CLI deployment command.
- DO NOT create or deploy to any other Vercel team (e.g. `one-booking`, `OneBooking`).
- DO NOT create new Vercel projects.
- DO NOT change the GitHub repository link.
- DO NOT log out of Vercel or switch teams unless the user explicitly asks.

## Allowed Vercel CLI Usage

These read/config commands ARE allowed (they don't deploy):

- `vercel env ls`, `vercel env add`, `vercel env rm`, `vercel env pull` (only on `royalwellnessspa`)
- `vercel inspect`, `vercel logs`
- `vercel link` (only to re-link to `lovedesignwork-8523s-projects/royalwellnessspa`)

## Environment Variable Updates

When env vars need to change:

1. Update them on the existing `royalwellnessspa` project via `vercel env add/rm`.
2. Push a trivial commit (or wait for the next code push) to trigger a fresh deploy.
3. Do not deploy via CLI.
